    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Candles held by members of a group in processions. Processional candles may be of various designs and sizes; the term includes both the candle and the fixtures that secure them, usually with candles mounted to a hand grip or pole, often within a protective shade or glass shield.</Note_Text>
